<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ890811-0140 </DOCNO><DD> = 890811 </DD><AN> 890811-0140. </AN><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:@  Scary Stories, Contd. </HL><DD> 08/11/89 </DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J) </SO><IN> ENVIRONMENT (ENV) </IN><TEXT>   Weeks have passed since some environmental group plopped a scary story onto the public, so we were overdue. It fell to the National Wildlife Federation to announce yesterday that based on its &quot;analysis&quot; of federal statistics and data banks, 500 companies have produced billions and billions of pounds of toxic waste in recent years. The mere assertion of this, of course, is expected to elicit horror and outrage from the usual quarters. No doubt it will, too. </TEXT></DOC>